Yes people, it's that time of year again! Ladies get your frocks at the ready and gents dust off your tuxedos 'cause Blackpool LIFE are holding yet another extravigant SUMMER BALL!!!

If you attended last year's Enchantment Over the Sea Dance then you'll know just what to expect. A classy evening compered by the dazzling ANNE NOLAN with live music from the Chameleon Jazz Band and the amazing MONSTER SQUAD!!

Set in the stunning, beautifully lit Victorian Sunlounge on the end of the north pier, this sophisticated evening promises to be filled with wonder and surprise as guests dance the night away in truly enchanting surroundings.

Delicious canapes will be served throughout the evening and the champagne will flow like wine!!

The shuttle bus will carry guests in true style from one end of the pier to the next where the red carpet will be rolled out!

All this for just £10 a ticket!!

For reservations either contact Laura on 07790280065 or go to The North Pier Box office.
Gigs.GigTitle: The Enchantment Over the Sea Dance

Imagine the technique and tone of Robin Trower, the feel of Bonnie Raitt, the inspiration of Hendrix, the influence of SRV, the energy of Bonamassa and the intensity of Trout all rolled into one. 

Chantel Mcgregor is one of the most exciting rock blues guitarists in the country.This is rock blues for the new age, played by a musician born with an effortless virtuosity, peppered by flights of incendiary guitar and flanked by moments of poise, grace and fluidity...
Chantel's debut album; Like No Other, showcases this, along with her genuine talent as a singer and songwriter.

Support from Callighan & Wolski.

Tickets £8 (adv) £10 (door) Tel 01253 887693

Situated in Lytham St Annes town centre directly opposite the railway station, The Town House, formerly known as the Crescent, is a trouble free, female friendly venue. Known as a lively, vibrant pub, it is part of the local circuit and prominent in the town. This modern style pub is open plan with bright colours and leather sofas where you can relax and enjoy a favourite pint or a value for money bite to eat. The bar, which is alongside the dance floor is a Victorian listed building and has a traditional feel.
